													<tr><td valign="top" width="100%">&nbsp;<br>
													<!-- strMainData goes here-->
													<table width='100%' cellpadding='3' border='0'>
<tr>
<td vAlign='absmiddle' align='left' width='80%' colSpan='4' bgcolor='#000000' class='header'><img border='0' src='./images/cricon.gif' align='absmiddle'> TEST OF TRUTH</td>
</tr>
<tr> 
<td width='80%'><p align="left">This quest originates in North Freeport, by Merkos Quentos.</p>
<p align="left">He resides at the Hall of Truth on the grassy area below the
Paladin Guildmaster, Valeron Dushire. This quest starts at about the 7th level,
and ranges through the 12th level to complete solo.</p>
<p align="left">If you say, &quot;I am a squire&quot; to Merkos, he will say
that he needs a small task. Little do you know that this will turn in to a major
undertaking. You then ask, &quot;What is the small task&quot;. He will give you
a note to give to Altunic Jartin in East Commonlands. You go to East Commonlands
and Altunic will normally be in a hut across from the 3rd Inn just before the
West Commonlands zone. If he is not there, just wait. He usually makes his
rounds through East Commonlands every once in a while. Give him the note and he
will say something about sending a squire to do a man's job and so forth. Then
he will ask you to take care of a problem rogue that keeps bothering him at his
house. Don't worry too much about the [house] part. If you say, &quot;Where is
your house&quot;, he will say, &quot;Follow me&quot;, but you are already there,
and I think it is broken anyway.</p>
<p align="left">At this time, Narls, the rogue, will be standing outside the
house shouting throughout the whole zone about how he is waiting for Jartin,
blah, blah, blah. Narls is about 6th level, I believe. He is hard to hit, and
has a pretty decent punch, twice a round. After killing him, you loot his body
for a head. After getting the head, give it to Altunic Jartin. After giving it
to Altunic, he then tells you that he likes to walk around and collect junk in
the area to sell. He is afraid of the denizens and would like to have a Cloth
Shirt to provide him with a little protection.</p>
<p align="left">You can buy a Cloth Shirt at the 2nd inn. Don't try a Small
Cloth Shirt, it will not work. A Cloth Shirt will cost around 5-6 gold to buy.
You can also find Cloth Shirts on certain mobs in the game. (orc centurions)
After getting the Cloth Shirt, give it to Altunic. He will say how wonderful and
noble you are and give you a coin called a &quot;Token of Generousity&quot;. He
will tell you to tell Merkos you have earned the token of generosity. (notice
the spelling, it is <u>very</u> important)</p>
<p align="left">Go to Merkos and say, &quot;I have earned the token of
generosity&quot;. You <u>must</u> spell it this way. He will then say that to
prove your bravery you have to fight a desert tarantula and get a spider venom
sac for him. I do not know if a venom sac from a dune tarantula will work, but
it might. If you decide to buy a spider venom sac, you might find one at the
inn, or the fishing village, in North Ro. They normally run about 5-6 gold. You
then give the spider venom sac to Merkos. He will then give you the &quot;Token
of Bravery&quot;. He will tell you that if you wish to go through the &quot;Test
of Truth&quot;, you must give him the tokens of generousity and bravery. Make
sure you can easily defeat a desert tarantula before doing this. </p>
<p align="left">The finale of this wonderful adventure is near. You give Merkos
the tokens of generousity and bravery one at a time, the order doesn't matter.
After the second token, Merkos will say something about your opponent being in
the sewer and to defeat them for the prize. This is very important, you must
move very quickly to the sewer, where the canoe is, and to the left is Guard
Willia. If you hesitate at all, Willia will run away, and you will lose your
chance. Guard Willia will plead with you to not kill him/her, and will try to
run away. The words [Freeport Militia] will appear in the paragraph, and if you
try to say something, they will be long gone. If anyone gets to say anything to
the Guard, please tell me what they say, if anything. I would guess the Guard is
about 12th level or so, a little harder than a desert tarantula. After killing
the Guard, you loot the body for a &quot;Token of Truth&quot;. If Guard Willia
runs away, he/she will say, &quot;Thank you for letting me go. I promise to
change my ways...Maybe!&quot;</p>
<p align="left">Give the token to Merkos, and he will give you 3 gold and a
testimony. To some people, 3 gold and a piece of paper are not worth the trouble
of this quest. I think that, being a Paladin, proving my loyalty and getting my
knighthood and recognition is quite a great reward for a &quot;Knight of
Truth&quot;.</p>
<p align="left">Sir Yeldarb SpiritBlade<br>
Paladin, Knight of Truth<br>
The Rathe</p></td>
</tr>
